    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0183"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mon. Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-06-25">June 25th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-06-25">June 25th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
            </opener>
           
            <p>
            Just a line to let you
            know I’m keeping track.  Kiffin
            wrote you about the loss of poor
            old Victor, the best and bravest
            of us all.  Somehow I can’t realize
            he’s gone, and when I think of it I
            feel so badly.  You know he had
            oranges in his machine to take to
            Balsley after the sortie.  It was like
            him.  We were all very fond of him.
            Everyone.  Yesterday I saw his machine
            leaning up against the hangar.  His 
            face was sad and he gazed off
            into the sky in the direction Victor
            had flown away.  Sometimes I keep
            looking over towards the lines
            hoping to see him coming.  If it only
            could have been some else. &mdash; Cowden, for
            instance or any like him.  No news.
            That nut Gros was out today. 
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <signed>Jim</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0184"/>
            
